The paper discusses the cooperation of multiple autonomous robots and the analysis of their swarm behavior, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). The paper also discusses the behavior of robots in a changing environment, which is related to robotics and control (cs.RO). The paper also presents a novel approach to model the behavior of robots, which can be related to systems and control (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the verification and analysis of the behavior of combined robots, which can be related to software engineering (cs.SE).
